Package edu.umd.cs.psl.model.predicate

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ExternalFunctionalPredicate
    A FunctionalPredicate which uses an ExternalFunction to compute truth values.
    FunctionalPredicate
    A Predicate with GroundAtoms that have truth values defined by a function of their arguments and the ObservedAtoms of the closed StandardPredicates of the GroundAtoms' Databases.
    Predicate
    A relation that can be applied to Terms to form Atoms.
    PredicateFactory
    The factory for Predicates.
    SpecialPredicate
    A commonly used FunctionalPredicate.
    StandardPredicate
    Predicate of GroundAtoms that can be persisted in a Database.
